In a joint press conference, Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos and US Vice President Mike Pence discussed a range of issues, including the peace process in Colombia, the fight against drug trafficking, and the situation in Venezuela. President Santos expressed gratitude for the US government's support in consolidating peace in Colombia, particularly in helping with the disarmament of the FARC and the reintegration of former members into civilian life. Vice President Pence emphasized the strong partnership between the US and Colombia, highlighting the economic ties between the two countries and the importance of addressing the drug crisis in Colombia. He also reiterated the US government's commitment to supporting efforts to restore democracy in Venezuela, condemning the Maduro regime and calling for increased diplomatic pressure. Both leaders emphasized the importance of a peaceful transition in Venezuela and ruled out the possibility of a military intervention.